import koalas as ks

ks_df.to_spark()

Common subexpression elimination: This technique replaces multiple occurrences of the same expression with a single occurrence, such as replacing “x + y” with “z” if “x + y” is always equal to “z”.
Loop unrolling: This technique replaces a loop with multiple copies of the loop body, which can improve the efficiency of the program by reducing the number of times the loop is executed.

Method inlining: This technique replaces a method call with the method’s body, which can improve the efficiency of the program by reducing the number of method calls.
